
 At least 50 people have died this morning following a bomblast attack at a Mosque in Mubi, Adamawa State North Eastern part of Nigeria.
 Nigerian local media have reported that the attack that is believed to have been executed by a suicide bomber took place in the morning hours, and it was targeting the worshippers at the mosque.
 A Statement from the Nigerian Police Spokesma Othman Abubakar confirmed the death of more than 50 people, and further indicated that militant group Boko Haram is suspected to have perpetrated the attack.




